              </row>
              <row halign="center">
                <cell><m>3.1</m></cell>
              </row>
            </tabular>
          </table> </p>
      </task>
      <task><p>Which of the following describe the behavior of the graph near <m>x=3</m>?
        <ol marker= "A.">  
        <li> As <m> x\to 3</m>, <m>r(x)</m> approaches a finite number</li>
        <li> As <m> x\to 3</m> from the left, <m>r(x)\to\infty</m></li>
        <li> As <m>x \to 3</m> from the left, <m>r(x)\to -\infty</m></li>
        <li> As <m>x \to 3</m> from the right, <m>r(x)\to \infty</m></li>
        <li> As <m>x \to 3</m> from the right, <m>r(x)\to -\infty</m></li></ol>
      </p>
      </task>
      <task>
        <p> The function was also not defined for <m>x=1</m>. Make a table for values of <m>r(x)</m> near <m>x=1</m>. 
          <table>
            <tabular>
              <row header="yes" bottom="minor" >
                <cell><m>x</m></cell> 
                <cell><m>r(x)</m></cell>
              </row>
              <row halign="center">
