              </row>
              <row halign="center">
                <cell><m>0.999</m></cell>
              </row>
              <row halign="center">
                <cell><m>1</m></cell>
                <cell>undefined</cell>
              </row>
              <row halign="center">
                <cell><m>1.001</m></cell>
              </row>
              <row halign="center">
                <cell><m>1.01</m></cell>
              </row>
              <row halign="center">
                <cell><m>1.1</m></cell>
              </row>
            </tabular>
          </table> </p>
      </task>
      <task><p>Which of the following describe the behavior of the graph near <m>x=1</m>?
        <ol marker= "A.">  
        <li> As <m> x\to 1</m>, <m>r(x)</m> approaches a finite number</li>
        <li> As <m> x\to 1</m> from the left, <m>r(x)\to\infty</m></li>
        <li> As <m>x \to 1</m> from the left, <m>r(x)\to -\infty</m></li>
        <li> As <m>x \to 1</m> from the right, <m>r(x)\to \infty</m></li>
        <li> As <m>x \to 1</m> from the right, <m>r(x)\to -\infty</m></li></ol>
      </p>
      </task>
      <task>
        <p>The function is behaving differently near <m>x=1</m> than it is near <m>x=3</m>. Can you see anything in the factored form of <m>r(x)</m> that may help you account for the difference? </p>
      </task>
